 {"id":"bd-mblr.4","title":"E2E Scenario Completeness","description":"Define and implement a complete end-to-end scenario matrix (DDL/DML/transactions/concurrency/recovery/corruption/compatibility) with deterministic reproducibility and artifact capture.","design":"Scenario completeness should be requirements-traceable, not ad-hoc test accumulation.","acceptance_criteria":"Scenario matrix published with full ownership; missing required scenarios implemented; deterministic replay metadata emitted; failure bundles complete.","notes":"Deferred intentionally for queue hygiene: this bead is a container/coordination umbrella, not a direct implementation lane. Work proceeds through its child tasks; reopen/close this bead during milestone rollup and completion review.","status":"deferred","priority":1,"issue_type":"epic","created_at":"2026-02-12T23:23:16.914003853Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-13T00:51:03.695330127Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.4","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-12T23:23:16.914003853Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.4","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-12T23:25:06.106603431Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":1341,"issue_id":"bd-mblr.4","author":"Dicklesworthstone","text":"Detailed scope: produce an explicit scenario ledger with owning tests and pass criteria. Completion is defined by closure of matrix gaps, not by raw test count growth. Every required scenario must have deterministic replay data.","created_at":"2026-02-12T23:26:03Z"}]}
 {"id":"bd-mblr.4.1","title":"Canonical E2E Scenario Matrix and Traceability","description":"Define required e2e scenarios and map each to tests/scripts: schema evolution, transactional semantics, concurrent writers, lock-contention edge cases, corruption/recovery, compatibility parity, and performance sanity. Include explicit pass criteria and owning test entrypoints.","design":"Represent scenario definitions as structured manifest entries so matrix evolution is reviewable and machine-consumable.","acceptance_criteria":"- Canonical scenario matrix covers transactional semantics, concurrency, recovery/corruption, compatibility, and sanity performance checks.
- Every scenario has stable scenario_id, explicit pass/fail oracle, and owning test/script entrypoint.
- Traceability map links scenario_id to expected logs and artifacts.","notes":"Matrix quality determines whether E2E coverage claims are defensible; avoid undocumented ad-hoc scenarios.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-12T23:24:06.665150148Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-13T00:05:22.407538410Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.4.1","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.1.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-12T23:25:09.983636915Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.4.1","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.4","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-12T23:24:06.665150148Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":1348,"issue_id":"bd-mblr.4.1","author":"Dicklesworthstone","text":"Scenario matrix should include: setup prerequisites, deterministic seed policy, expected assertions, required artifacts on failure, and explicit command to run each scenario.","created_at":"2026-02-12T23:26:13Z"}]}
